    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-18T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="565"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/727</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-18T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 19, 7.51 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. <persName corresp="#p_HP1">Hymans</persName>, replying tonight to your 291
                    April 12,<note n="1" xml:id="d565fn1">See last sentence in telegram of Apr. 11,
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_475">p. 475</ref>.</note>
                    says the feeding of the population already so tried would be imperiled if the
                    tonnage used for shipping food were reduced and that new privations would
                    enfeeble their moral resistance. Under these conditions he says, “The Government
                    of the King regrets that it is not able to give its assent to the proposed
                    measure.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
